22/06/2004
STRASBOURG, France -- The Council of Europe Parliamentary Assembly approved a report Monday (21 June) that recommends closing the monitoring procedure for Turkey. The procedure, which covers human rights issues, has been in effect since 1996. Its closure is a main prerequisite to meeting the Copenhagen political criteria for EU membership.
In other news, Turkish police announced on Monday the seizure of 103kg of heroin at Kapikule Border Gate in Edrine province, along the border with Bulgaria. The estimated value of the seized drug is $9.4m. (Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News, TRT 2, NTV - 21/06/04)
